edu.wit.dcsn.comp2000.list.adt

Class LinkedList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wit.dcsn.comp2000.list.adt.LinkedList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the class of objects to be stored in the list such that T implements the Comparable interface.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ListInterface<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>

    public class LinkedList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ListInterface<T>
    A class that implements the ADT list by using a chain of nodes that has both a head reference and a tail reference. This implementation is Iterable using an inner class iterator. Two additional methods are required: sort() and shuffle().
    Version:
    4.0, 5.0, 4.1.0 2018-07-11
    • initial version based upon Carrano and Henry implementation in the 4th edition of the textbook
    • modified per assignment
    , 5.1.0 2019-07-14
    • revise to match the 5th edition of the textbook
    • revise to match this semester's assignment
    • switch from 1-based to 0-based positions
    , 5.2.0 2019-11-12 track revised assignment for this semester, 5.3.0 2020-07-17
    • move Node inner class to separate class
    • update to coding standard
    • streamline some code
    • add array constructor
    • prevent add(null)
    • switch to EnhancedListInterface from ListInterface and Iterable
    , 5.4.0 2020-11-09
    • track changes/consolidation to ListInterface
      • remove explicit implements Iterable
      • rename class from EnhancedLinkedList to LinkedList
    • replace toString() and implement main() as a testing/debugging aid
    , 5.5.0 2020-11-09 implement sort() and shuffle()
    Author:
    Frank M. Carrano, Timothy M. Henry, David M Rosenberg, Your Name // TODO

        private void interleave(Node<T> firstHalf,

        Utility method to re-populate the instance chain from the two sub-chains.

        Preconditions:

        • the instance variables (firstNode and lastNode) are both null
        • both sub-chains are null-terminated
        Parameters:
        firstHalf - a reference to one sub-chain containing ~1/2 of the elements in the instance - reconstruction of the instance chain will begin with the first entry in this sub-chain (if any)
        secondHalf - a reference to the other sub-chain
